# Cursor Project Rules for Leader Leap Dashboard

## Code Modification Rules
- NEVER modify the logic inside hooks without explicit permission
- NEVER use db reset without explicit permission
- Always ask for consent before making any code changes
- Explain changes before implementing them

## Database Rules
- All schema changes must go through Supabase migrations
- Standalone SQL files are for manual maintenance only
- Never create new standalone SQL files without explicit need
- Always verify current database state before suggesting changes

## Security Rules
- Security changes require explicit approval
- Never modify RLS policies without thorough explanation
- Always consider security implications of database changes

## Project Conventions
- Follow existing code patterns and conventions
- Use TypeScript types consistently
- Maintain existing file structure
- Respect the current tech stack (Vite, React, Supabase)

## Communication Rules
- Proceed step-by-step and ask for consent
- Explain the reasoning behind suggestions
- Provide context for all recommendations 